<GUIClass name="CM_GroupingTable" id="d1f00324-3c0d-4551-9551-1da50431389e">
    <superclass name="CM_DataTable"/>
    <transient/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>
1. You will need to nominate a row in your entTableView as the grouping row.
1. Use the setTblDataEntRowsFromView_Grp method instead of setTblDataEntRowsFromView to set table columns.  
   This allows you to specify which row to group on.
2. Always use addItemObject/addItemObjectAt to add detail lines to the table
3. If the text you pass to the above method does not contain a value for the item you are grouping on then
   use the updateGroupingValue method to set this value for the item you are adding.
4. If you clear the table, then use the clearGroups method before reloading.
5. Only 4 user defined sort columns supported.
6. Use the groupHeadingDisplay method to return the text to be displayed as a group heading for a given row value
7. If you are displaying calculated values in your group headings, use the refreshGroupHeadings to redisplay headinss</text>
    <DbClassMap file="_usergui"/>
